#: ../../includes_knife/includes_knife_serve.rst:6
# eed8ddd3061549c482b2ee2072ad3d4d
msgid "The |subcommand knife serve| subcommand is used to run a persistent |chef zero| against the local |chef repo|. (|chef zero| is a lightweight |chef server| that runs in-memory on the local machine.) This is the same as running the |chef client| executable with the ``--local-mode`` option. The ``chef_repo_path`` is located automatically and the |chef server| will bind to port ``8900`` by default. |subcommand knife serve| will print the URL for the local |chef server|, so that it may be added to the |knife rb| file."
msgstr ""

